
1. 	POJO stands for Plane Old Java Object and Java Bean class is also a POJO class but with some
	advancement added in it to access object's.
	
2.	POJO is simple java class which can be accessed by anyone and it doesn't implements or extends
	any other class or interface. But in bean class to get or set values to the variables we have
	to go throw certain getter and setter methods.
	
3.	POJO class can be any class which has zero argument constructor and not implementing or extending
	other classes or interface but bean class is a encapsulated class whose variable values can be
	access only by some getter and setter methods.